# Cisco Introduction to Cybersecurity

## Course Overview
- Duration: ~6 hours
- Level: Beginner
- Format: Self-paced, labs, quizzes
- Goal: Fundamentals of cybersecurity, online safety, threats, defense, careers

## Module 1: Cybersecurity Basics
- Definition & importance
- Impact on individuals, businesses, governments
- CIA Triad: Confidentiality, Integrity, Availability

## Module 2: Online Safety
- Safe browsing practices
- Strong passwords & MFA
- Phishing & social engineering
- Privacy & data confidentiality

## Module 3: Cyber Threats
- Malware: viruses, worms, trojans, ransomware, spyware
- Attacks: DoS/DDoS, SQL injection, MITM
- Vulnerabilities in networks/software

## Module 4: Defense Strategies
- Firewalls & IDS/IPS
- Encryption methods
- Security policies & best practices

## Module 5: Cybersecurity Careers
- Roles: SOC Analyst, Pen Tester, Security Engineer
- Certifications: CCNA Security, CompTIA Security+, CISSP
- Global demand for professionals

## Key Skills Learned
- Threat detection
- Identifying network vulnerabilities
- Cybersecurity best practices
- Privacy & confidentiality protection


